===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# [[similar]], or the [[same]] as something else
# having the same [[composition]] throughout; [[uniform]]
# {{chemistry}} in the same [[state of matter]].
# {{mathematics}} Of which the properties of a smaller set apply to the whole; [[scalable]].
## {{mathematics}} A function is homogeneous of degree-''k'' if scaling all arguments by α scales the output by α<sup>''k''</sup>.
##: The function ''f(x)=x<sup>2</sup>'' is homogeneous of degree 2 because ''f(''α''x)=''α''<sup>2</sup>f(x)''.

